  "utm.ponder.oxygen_collector.intro.header": "Collecting Oxygen",
  "utm.ponder.oxygen_collector.intro.text_1": "The Oxygen Collector condenses oxygen from the surrounding area",
  "utm.ponder.oxygen_collector.intro.text_2": "You can pump LOX from its internal tank",
  "utm.ponder.oxygen_collector.intro.text_3": "On planets without oxygen the collector can be surrounded in up to 7³ leaves",
  "utm.ponder.oxygen_collector.intro.text_4": "The more leaves and the higher the RPM, the more efficient it is!",
  "utm.ponder.oxygen_collector.intro.text_5": "* This functionality is shared with the backtank",

  "utm.ponder.oxygen_furnace.intro.header": "Creating Steel",
  "utm.ponder.oxygen_furnace.intro.text_1": "The Oxygen Furnace produces molten steel when provided with the right inputs",
  "utm.ponder.oxygen_furnace.intro.text_2": "The Oxygen Furnace requires coal, iron, and LOX",
  "utm.ponder.oxygen_furnace.intro.text_3": "The resulting molten steel can then be pressed into steel ingots and sheets",

  "utm.ponder.ion_jet.intro.header": "Basic Rocketry - Electric Propulsion",
  "utm.ponder.ion_jet.intro.text_1": "The Ion Jet is a low powered high efficiency thruster for long distance travel in space",
  "utm.ponder.ion_jet.intro.text_2": "When provided with LOX and a constant RPM it will begin producing thrust",
  "utm.ponder.ion_jet.intro.text_3": "Umlike other kinetic components the Ion Jet has no limits on maximum RPM or thrust, as long as you can keep it powered",

  "utm.ponder.liquid_thruster.intro.header": "Basic Rocketry - Liquid Propulsion",
  "utm.ponder.liquid_thruster.intro.text_1": "The Liquid Fuel Thruster is a simple device",
  "utm.ponder.liquid_thruster.intro.text_2": "When provided with lava and redstone the thruster will activate",
  "utm.ponder.liquid_thruster.intro.text_3": "Throttle is tied to redstone strength, but higher throttles will consume more fuel",

  "utm.ponder.solid_thruster.intro.header": "Basic Rocketry - Solid Propulsion",
  "utm.ponder.solid_thruster.intro.text_1": "The Solid Rocket Thruster is the simplest method of rocket propulsion",
  "utm.ponder.solid_thruster.intro.text_2": "When activated with redstone all connected coal/charcoal blocks are marked as fuel",
  "utm.ponder.solid_thruster.intro.text_3": "As the thruster burns fuel will be consumed in order of farthest to nearest",
  "utm.ponder.solid_thruster.intro.text_4": "The more thrusters you use connected to a line of fuel, the more efficient they are",
  "utm.ponder.solid_thruster.intro.text_5": "Happy Engineering!",

